+# Research Document: terraphim-ai v1.20.3 Release Blockers
+
+**Status**: Approved
+**Author**: Claude Code
+**Date**: 2026-06-13
+**Investigation method**: SSH to bigbox (`ssh bigbox`), live codebase grep
+
+---
+
+## Executive Summary
+
+Five release blockers exist across two tracks. Track A (three infra issues) freezes CI
+and must land first; Track B (two security/code issues) must land before shipping the
+binary. One supplementary finding (flaky benchmark) also blocks a clean `cargo test --workspace`.
+
+---
+
+## Track A — Infra
+
+### #2610 — CI frozen: all jobs fail at step 1
+
+**Live evidence** (bigbox, 2026-06-13):
+
+```
+● terraphim-gitea-runner.service
+   Active: active (running) since Thu 2026-06-11 20:26:49 CEST
+   Memory: 717.1M (peak: 7.3G)
+
+Runner config: ~/.config/terraphim-gitea-runner/.runner
+  "labels": ["terraphim-native"]
+
+Workflow: .gitea/workflows/native-ci.yml
+  runs-on: terraphim-native    ← labels match, runner IS dispatching jobs
+
+Every job in journal (Jun 11 – Jun 13):
+  [INFO] Executing step 1/5: cargo fmt --all -- --check
+  [INFO] Released session … task complete: success=false   ← fails in <1s
+```
+
+The label mismatch described in the original issue title is resolved. The current
+failure is caused entirely by the rustup wrapper bug documented in #2462.
+
+---
+
+### #2462 — rustup wrapper argv[0] bug (causes #2610)
+
+**Live evidence** (bigbox):
+
+```
+~/.cargo/bin/cargo  →  rustup  (bash wrapper script)
+
+Contents of ~/.cargo/bin/rustup:
+  #!/usr/bin/env bash
+  export RUSTUP_REAL="/home/alex/.cargo/bin/rustup.real"
+  exec "/home/alex/.local/bin/rustup-with-perms.sh" "$@"
+
+Contents of ~/.local/bin/rustup-with-perms.sh (relevant line):
+  "$RUSTUP_REAL" "$@"          ← BUG: argv[0] is "rustup.real", not "cargo"
+
+Reproducer:
+  $ cargo fmt --all -- --check
+  error: unexpected argument '--all' found
+    tip: to pass '--all' as a value, use '-- --all'
+  Usage: rustup[EXE] <+toolchain>
+
+Toolchain binaries (NOT the root cause):
+  ls -la ~/.rustup/toolchains/stable-x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu/bin/
+  -rwxr-xr-x ... cargo
+  -rwxr-xr-x ... rustfmt
+  (execute bits are present — the original +x problem IS fixed)
+```
+
+**Root cause**: `rustup.real` uses `argv[0]` to decide whether it is acting as `rustup`
+or as a cargo/rustfmt/etc. proxy. The wrapper calls it as `rustup.real` (not `cargo`),
+so it processes subcommands as rustup commands, not cargo commands.
+
+**Fix** — one line change in `/home/alex/.local/bin/rustup-with-perms.sh`:
+```bash
+# Before:
+"$RUSTUP_REAL" "$@"
+# After:
+exec -a "$(basename "$0")" "$RUSTUP_REAL" "$@"
+```
+
+---
+
+### #2608 — Ports 6666 and 8095 bound on all interfaces
+
+**Live evidence** (bigbox, `sudo lsof -i :6666 -i :8095`):
+
+```
+PORT 6666:
+  bun  3384585  martin  14u  IPv6  TCP *:6666 (LISTEN)
+  Command: bun run src/mentor.ts
+  CWD: ~/qa-work/odilo-slack-local/services/stubs/
+  Running since: May 18
+
+PORT 8095:
+  bun  3384592  martin  180u  IPv6  TCP *:8095 (LISTEN)
+  Command: bun --watch src/index.ts
+  Running since: May 18
+```
+
+These are not Terraphim processes. They are Slack bot stub services belonging to user
+`martin`, started in a persistent tmux session. Both bind to `*:` (all network
+interfaces) instead of `127.0.0.1`.
+
+**Fix**: Contact martin to add `HOST=127.0.0.1` to the bun startup, or apply a ufw rule:
+```bash
+sudo ufw deny in on eth0 to any port 6666
+sudo ufw deny in on eth0 to any port 8095
+```
+
+---
+
+## Track B — Code / Security
+
+### #2519 — Ed25519 public key needs production keying
+
+**Live evidence** (`crates/terraphim_update/src/signature.rs`):
+
+```
+Line 28: // TODO: Replace with actual Terraphim AI public key after key generation
+Line 29: // Run: ./scripts/generate-zipsign-keypair.sh
+Line 30: // Then add the public key here
+Line 36: "1uLjooBMO+HlpKeiD16WOtT3COWeC8J/o2ERmDiEMc4="
+
+Line 135 (placeholder guard):
+  if key_str.starts_with("TODO:") {          ← only blocks "TODO:" prefix
+      return Err(anyhow!("Placeholder..."));  ← current key does NOT trigger this
+  }
+
+.github/workflows/release-sign.yml:86:
+  ZIPSIGN_PRIVATE_KEY: ${{ secrets.ZIPSIGN_PRIVATE_KEY }}
+```
+
+The embedded public key at line 36 has a TODO comment indicating it has not been
+formally confirmed as the production key. The CI signing workflow uses
+`${{ secrets.ZIPSIGN_PRIVATE_KEY }}` — if that secret does not hold the private key
+matching this exact public key, all signed releases will fail verification on users'
+machines. The script to generate a new pair exists at
+`scripts/generate-zipsign-keypair.sh`.
+
+---
+
+### #2415 — KG validator never called on hot path
+
+**Live evidence** (`crates/terraphim_rlm/src/`):
+
+```
+validator.rs:198
+  pub struct KnowledgeGraphValidator { … }
+
+rlm.rs:310 — execute_code():
+  self.session_manager.validate_session(session_id)?;  ← validates UUID only
+  // NO call to self.validator.validate(code)
+  self.executor.execute_code(code, &ctx).await
+
+rlm.rs:366 — execute_command():
+  self.session_manager.validate_session(session_id)?;  ← validates UUID only
+  // NO call to self.validator.validate(command)
+  self.executor.execute_command(command, &ctx).await
+
+query_loop.rs:
+  grep KnowledgeGraphValidator → 0 results
+  grep validate             → 0 results
+```
+
+`KnowledgeGraphValidator` is tested in isolation in `validator.rs` unit tests but is
+never wired into `TerraphimRlm` or `QueryLoop`. Any command or code string passes
+straight to execution without KG term matching.
+
+---
+
+## Supplementary Findings
+
+### cargo test --workspace failure
+
+```
+crates/terraphim_tinyclaw/tests/skills_benchmarks.rs:142
+  FAILED: benchmark_execution_small_skill
+  Skill execution took too long: 4.508551771s
+```
+
+The test asserts a hard wall-clock time bound which fails on a loaded CI host. Must
+be fixed (tighter implementation, or `#[ignore]` with explanation) before declaring
+a clean workspace test run.
+
+### crates/terraphim_settings/ — untracked but intentional
+
+`Cargo.toml:27` explicitly excludes `crates/terraphim_settings` as part of polyrepo
+extraction E2 (Gitea #1910). The directory contains residual files from the extraction.
+Not a blocker.
+
+### Version drift in non-workspace Cargo.tomls
+
+| Crate | Current version | Workspace version | File |
+|-------|----------------|-------------------|------|
+| terraphim_workspace | 1.13.0 | 1.20.3 | `crates/terraphim_workspace/Cargo.toml:3` |
+| terraphim_ai_nodejs | 1.19.2 | 1.20.3 | `terraphim_ai_nodejs/Cargo.toml:4` |
+
+Both use hardcoded `version = "x.y.z"` instead of `version.workspace = true`. Not a
+build blocker but creates misleading version metadata in published crates.
+
+---
+
+## Fix Sequence
+
+1. **bigbox hotfix** — `rustup-with-perms.sh` exec -a fix → unblocks all CI (fixes #2462, #2610)
+2. **Port restriction** — martin to bind to 127.0.0.1 or ufw rule (closes #2608)
+3. **Production keypair** — generate, store in 1P, update signature.rs, set GH secret (fixes #2519)
+4. **Wire KG validator** — add `validator` field to `TerraphimRlm`, guard `execute_code` and `execute_command` (fixes #2415)
+5. **Version alignment** — `version.workspace = true` in two Cargo.toml files
+6. **Flaky benchmark** — fix timing test in terraphim_tinyclaw
